    "lesson_content_markdown":  "# Finished Past: Special Spellings\n\nMany common words in English do NOT use **-ed** for the past. They change in special ways. We call these **Irregular Verbs**.\n\n### 1. Common Word Changes\n\n- **Go** â†’ **Went** (I went to class.)\n- **Eat** â†’ **Ate** (They ate lunch.)\n- **Write** â†’ **Wrote** (She wrote a letter.)\n- **See** â†’ **Saw** (We saw the teacher.)\n- **Read** â†’ **Read** (Same word, but sounds like the color \u0027red\u0027)\n\n### 2. Time (Be Verbs)\n\n- **Am / Is** â†’ **Was**\n- **Are** â†’ **Were**\n\n- **Example**: Yesterday, I **was** in the library. \n- **Example**: They **were** happy after the test.\n\n### 3. Having and Doing\n\n- **Have** â†’ **Had**\n- **Do** â†’ **Did**\n\n- **Example**: He **had** a long lunch break.\n- **Example**: We **did** our homework together.\n\n---",
